name: Bright, Modern Garden Unit - 1BR/1BTH
description:
Our bright garden unit overlooks a lovely backyard area with fruit trees and native plants. It is an oasis in a big city. The apartment comfortably fits a couple or small family. It is located on a cul de sac street that ends at lovely Duboce Park.

The space
Newly remodeled, modern, and bright garden unit in historic Victorian home.

New fixtures and finishes.
Zero VOC and non-toxic paint.
Organic and fair-trade teas, fresh local ground coffee.
Local art on walls.
Sofa bed and Queen bed are in the same room. More of a petite apartment with a separate room for dining and kitchen.

Guest access
Full access to patio and backyard (Shared)
Beautiful garden with fruit trees & native plants
Washer & dryer (Shared)
Children's toys
Charcoal grill

Other things to note
Due to the fact that we have children and a dog, we are up early 7-8am and their footsteps or paws can be heard
neighborhood_overview:
Quiet cul de sac in friendly neighborhood
Steps away from grassy park with 2 playgrounds and Recreational Center
Very family-friendly neighborhood
Quaint shops, grocery stores and restaurants all within a 5-10 minute walk
host_about: We are a family of four that live upstairs.  We have a large dog who occasionally can be seen in the backyard. We have lived in our home since 2005 and have been renting our apartment since 2008.

name: Creative Sanctuary
description:
We live in a large Victorian house on a quiet street, nestled between the Mission district and Noe Valley. We're one block from the streetcar stop and five blocks from the subway. We have two bedrooms which have double beds and windows which cast their light upon the warm colored walls and ceilings of this haven. We have lots of spaces in the house where you can relax, read, listen to music and just cozy up. The kitchen is well stocked and we have a bountiful garden and back deck.

The space

host_about:
Philip: English transplant to the Bay Area and half Spanish adoptive son of hardworking Yorkshire folk. I'm married to the one, engaged to my work and in love with exploring the merging of design art and craft.

Tania: SF raised with a NY energy and an Armenian background that I am proud of. I'm an international journalist, interviewing artists and producing for radio and print. I speak several languages and love to meet people. Found my husband in a cafe in NY and came back to SF to live near my Grandma. Oh, and I love plants.

name: Mission Sunshine, with Private Bath
description:
Welcome to "The Mission," the sunniest neighborhood in town. Enjoy world-class dining, shopping, and nightlife on Valencia, or a Tartine picnic in Dolores Park, all just steps from our 100 year old home.
We've been Hosts since Airbnb's 1st year (2009), and can suggest restaurants or insider sight-seeing ideas. We love our home, our hometown, and our neighborhood, and we look forward to sharing them with you.
PLEASE click below to read more about this private room and bath in a shared home.

The space
Your sunny room looks out over a lush garden, and includes all the comforts of home... Queen bed, sofa, dresser, closet, and a rocking chair.

Just up the hall, your private bathroom has a "like rain" shower head over a clawfoot tub. (The bathroom is not "en-suite.")

For a third guest (or for two guests who want separate beds) there is a full second bedroom available. ($60/night, and only available if you book Mission Sunshine.)
<
neighborhood_overview:
Located between Valencia Street and Dolores Park, we are in a great location for exploring the Mission, as well as the rest of San Francisco. It's an easy walk to the Castro, Haight Street, Hayes Valley, and Noe Valley. And we're close to BART and Muni, so it's easy to visit the Ferry Building, Union Square, Downtown... Everywhere!

Then again, you might not want to leave the neighborhood at all... Here's a very incomplete list of spots within 4 blocks of our home:

Foodie Heaven: Tartine, Delfina, Bi Rite Market, Mission Chinese Food, Foreign Cinema, BiRite Creamery, the list goes on - and seems to grow daily!

Shopping: 826 Valencia (Dave Eggers' Pirate Supply Store!), Paxton Gate, Curiosities for Kids, Beta Brand, Mission Bicycle, Self Edge, Weston Wear, Shoe Biz...

Dolores Park, the Chapel (for live music), Clarion Alley (home to the CAMP Mural project), the Women's Building (maybe the most famous of the famous Mission Murals), Mission Poo
host_about:
Ivan is a publisher of a book for 4 year olds. (Look for "Four is a little, Four is a LOT" or "fourlosophy".) Wendy is an elementary school teacher. And Milo is a 25 pound mutt. (Terrier...? Chihuahua...? Pinscher...? Perhaps. Sweet...? Charming...? Adorable...? Absolutely!) 
We've hosted continuously since 2009 - the year Airbnb nÃ©e "AirBedAndBreakfast" began! We love our home, our hometown, and our neighborhood, and we look forward to sharing them with you. We'll happily make dining recommendations, share insider sight-seeing ideas, and hopefully help you have a great visit.

name: Stylish, Spacious and Quiet Flat!
description:
***Will consider small pets. One pet per stay***

Stylish, clean and quiet Edwardian in a great safe neighborhood with easy access to every part of the city. It's a perfect space to relax after a day of activities.

The space
The flat is a stylish, spacious, clean and quiet 2 bedroom, 1 bathroom Edwardian. It is 1200 square feet which is a good size for San Francisco.

There is a very comfortable queen size bed in each room and it's fairly sunny during the day (unless we're fogged in) and pretty dark and quiet in the evenings (perfect for sleeping). I also have a twin size cot with a memory foam mattress that fits into bedroom 2. It's super comfortable and great if you need two beds in a room.

Guest access
You will have access to the entire apartment during your stay.

My sister lives in the upstairs flat with a separate entrance.

Other things to note
My sister lives in the flat above m
neighborhood_overview:
Experience the real San Francisco and stay where the locals live. Whether you're visiting for business or pleasure, the Richmond District is the perfect location. This is a quiet, safe neighborhood which makes it great for families. Parking can be tricky in San Francisco which makes my area a bit more desirable if you have a car as parking tends to be a bit easier versus other neighborhoods. It is further away from the main tourist attractions, but still accessible.

A great change of scenery during pandemic times. Everyone in the neighborhood wears masks and practices social distancing. There are lots of outdoor dining options in the area as well as great parks, beaches and hikes that are walking distance.

You're just a 15 minute walk to Baker Beach, a 15 minute walk to Presidio, a 20 minute walk to Golden Gate Park and 12 blocks from Lincoln Park Golf Course. The Legion of Honor, The DeYoung Museum and Land's End (Coastal Trail that runs about six miles a
host_about: Like most San Franciscans, eating good food and trying all types of restaurants is one of my favorite past times. I enjoy cooking, entertaining and listening to live music. I have as much fun doing indoor activities (IE: reading, watching movies, dancing), as I do outdoor activities (IE: hiking, kayaking, scuba diving). I live for a weekend getaway whether itâ€™s planned or spontaneous. I consider wine tasting through any wine region a good way to spend the day, and I am in constant search of the perfect beach.  I work in the Travel Industry, so my short list gets longer and longer. I'm an avid home exchanger as well!

room in a 2 bedroom near it all in the Mission District, including BART. Internet, parking if you want, $10/night. name: Central San Francisco Urban Dream
description:
3 BR/2 BA Victorian flat beautifully restored with all the charming details, the comfort of modern amenities plus a beautiful garden to hang out in. One block to public transportation, walking distance to many great restaurants, shops and parks.

The space
3 BR/2 BA Victorian flat beautifully restored with all the charming details, the comfort of modern amenities plus a beautiful garden to hang out in. We are in the Lower Haight neighborhood (not Hayes Valley). Muni train 2 blocks away, several buses less than 1 block away. Walking distance to Haight Ashbury, NOPA, Hayes Valley and Castro restaurants, bars, shops and Golden Gate Park. We're close to the geographic center of San Francisco so you can get to the best neighborhoods easily from here.
There's loads of space for you and your family or friends. Come back to a comfortable, homey place after your day exploring the city. We are both travelers and explorers and have lots of info and maps of the r
neighborhood_overview:
Nearby market: Right out the front door, right at the corner. At the next corner (Haight and Scott) organic market on the right, regular corner store on the left

Big Grocery: Safeway at Market and Church

Cafe/coffee: For Haight street character: Cafe International (Haight and Fillmore); For a decent place to go with your laptop: Bean There (Steiner and Waller); For the Frenchie feel: Le Cafe du Soleil (Fillmore and Waller). Slightly further but very cute for breakfast/brunch: Cafe Flore (Market and Noe). If you are a coffee connoisseur - The Mill (Divisadero and Fulton)

Drinks: Famous for its beer on tap: Toronado (Haight between Steiner and Fillmore; get a sausage at Rosamunde next door while you are there); Funky: The Noc Noc (a few doors towards Steiner, next to Toronado); Trendy, fancy cocktails: Maven (Haight and Steiner). Several good bars at Divisadero between Fell and Fulton too (Madrone, MiniBar, the bar at NOPA, Fly Bar).
host_about: I am American of Indian decent and I live here with my husband who is Guatemalan and French and our dog (of unknown decent), Leela.  I've been in the bay area for 12 years so will have lots of travel ideas for you.  We love our home and would love to share it with a few good travelers.

name: Lake Street Single Family Home
description:
Our full-time home (available when we are away), is your perfect place to call "home base" as you explore the city or visit friends.

The space
Great open floor plan home on a quiet tree lined street in one of San Francisco's most coveted neighborhoods. Walking distance to the Presidio, Mountain Lake Park, Laurel Village, Sacramento St shopping and Golden Gate Park. Easy walk to many cafes and restaurants.

The first level features a sunny gourmet kitchen with top-of-the-line appliances, open kitchen/dining area/family area, a lovely foyer, living room with flat panel TV/DirectTV, and a full bathroom with a large whirlpool soaking tub. There is also a small laundry room on this level. There is a deck off kitchen with a Weber grill and the small backyard features a grassy area and patio seating. The second floor has 3 BR's - 1st BR with a Queen Bed, 2nd BR has a full bed and 3rd BR has a twin bed + a twin trundle. A pack-n-play is also available.

description:
A cute studio with nice street views and lots of light and easy access to a shared roof deck with awesome Golden Gate views.

Great, classic "Old Frisco" neighborhood.

New double-pane windows help keep out the sounds of the city.

The space
Features: Elevator, Wood floors, TV, DVD Player, Internet, Cable, Roof-top deck.

Kitchen: Stove, Microwave, Coffee maker, Toaster, Oven, Pots and Pans, Dishwasher, Dishes.

Beds: 1 Double bed(s).

Extras: Dryer, Washer, Towels, Toilet paper.


Charming studio located in residential and undeniably charming Nob Hill, San Francisco's most desirable destination. One block from Grace Cathedral and easy walking distance to famous Union Square shopping, the theatre district, Chinatown, and Fishermen's Wharf. Or hop on a cable car or grab a bus on the corner. Rather stay local? Walk over to Huntington Park or check out the neighborhood's many bars, bistros, and ea
neighborhood_overview:
Very centrally located.

Fishermans Wharf, Chinatown, North Beach, downtown, Union Square shopping, Polk Street action, are all within walking distant.

For those who prefer to ride, public transport, including the classic cable car lines, are conveniently close.

Nob Hill is Old San Francisco, filled with the cable cars and classic Victorian architecture the city is famous for.

It's also a rich neighborhood with luxury buildings and nice restaurants and expansive views of the bay and beyond. There are a Trader Joes and a Whole Foods within walking distance, not to mention a cute gourmet market on the corner one block up.

For the party-minded, Polk Street and its remarkable night life are just three blocks away.
host_about:
I'm a writer, and encourage visiting writers and editors to use this studio. This is a historic building on Nob Hill, convenient to everything. Dashiell Hammett lived in this building and, we are told, finished The Maltese Falcon here. We bought this studio to house our son while he was in college; now we rent it to tourists and visiting professionals.

We are very interested in swapping housing also.

name: Comfortable space of your own in SF
description:
The space
A beautiful, bright, and spacious San Francisco studio apartment, located in the Richmond district, is available for short term rental. It's a perfect size for a single traveler, a couple, or a small family who are looking for more budget accommodations in this expensive city.

The kitchen is equipped with a full-sized refrigerator, microwave, toaster oven, coffee pot, and electric kettle, perfect for having simple breakfasts at home before starting your day of sightseeing. Please be aware that the kitchen does not have a stove top range or full sized oven. The bathroom is very large and clean and has a shower over the bathtub. There is a comfortable queen-sized bed that sleeps 2, as well as a sofa bed, which can accommodate another 2 guests (if your reservation is only for 2 guests and you request both the bed and sofa bed, there is an additional linen fee assessed) . This set up is more suitable for a family rather than 2 couples, however, as there is
neighborhood_overview: The location is not considered a traditionally 'touristy' part of the city, but rather more of a neighborhood for San Francisco residents. That being said, Golden Gate Park (home of the De Young museum, California Academy of Sciences, Japanese Tea Garden, and many other attractions), Ocean Beach, Baker Beach, the Golden Gate Bridge, and the Presidio National Park are all nearby. Grocery shopping is simple as there are numerous produce markets and a large supermarket located within easy walking distance of the apartment. neighborhood_overview: Cole Valley is a small, family-friendly community in the geographical center of the city. Tree-shaded streets are lined with well-kept Victorian homes, and a variety of mom-and-pop shops and relaxed restaurants, including a 1930s-inspired soda fountain. The neighborhood offers hiking at the compact Tank Hill Park, with its panoramic views, or through the dense eucalyptus forest of the Mount Sutro Open Space Reserve.
host_about:
I am an Irish native living in the Desert. My 'Joie de Vivre' is all about entertainment, adventure, travel, the arts in all forms, food and wine (in no particular order) and my home reflects all of this. My wife Jill is an interior designer drawn to atypical, bold, eclectic design yet her works reflect a timeless beauty. Our home is a collaboration of both of our tastes. You will find a kitchen that is compact, efficient & chef clad surrounded by a dining room, living room, two bedrooms and a bathroom that have all been lovingly curated by us both. 
During Covid we both 'worked from home' and were grateful to have this very spacious home in Palm Springs. We managed to integrate it into a magical 'work from home' space offering two dedicated work spaces... one in the master bedroom on a 1960's Paul Puccio pink Onyx desk or additional large L-Shaped work space and the second more formal work desk in another bedroom whereby we custom built a 7' marble desk. The 'work from home' experience is nothing short of perfect with upgraded wifi and Eero ProMesh wifi throughout.

The condo has very high ceilings with skylights enabling it to be a bright & airy space. The layout is like a loft with one wide open space encom
neighborhood_overview: Bernal Heights was voted the best San Francisco neighborhood to live in.   It's a village within a city with lovely views, cafes & restaurants, parks, a library, a great bakery and grocery stores.   If you enjoy running or hiking, it's a perfect place to visit because you get the best of both worlds.  Also right down the hill is the Mission District which is chock-filled with restaurants, clubs and shops.  The top of Bernal Heights offers a spectacular 360 degree view of the city and the bay.  For those who have a car, there is plenty  free street parking on Ripley or adjacent streets in Bernal Heights during the day.  In the evenings, when neighbors return from work you may have to park in adjacent streets in the neighborhood.  Staying in  Bernal Heights during your visit to San Francisco will make you feel like you are an "insider" rather than a visitor living in a hotel downtown.
host_about:
I am a LEGAL San Francisco Short Term Rental Host and possess both a San Francisco STR Permit and a Business License.

San Francisco has been my home now for 30 years and I love my condo, my neighborhood and my city!  

I've lived in many places abroad and in the US but by far, San Francisco is my favorite place in the whole wide world.   

Having said that, I would like to visit the whole wide world!!  

I love to travel and enjoy meeting new and interesting people.  I am passionate about music and enjoy almost anything to do with the Arts.  On a cold rainy day I love a good book or movie.  I especially appreciate good company and good conversation but I also like my privacy and alone time. I am a foodie and am always looking for good restaurants or eateries and am blessed that San Francisco has many of these. 

I totally subscribe to living a sustainable life-style and appreciate if you join me in creating a greener planet.  California now suffers from frequent droughts so we are very conscientious here about not wasting water. I encourage my guests to conserve both water and energy, even during wet years. 

Suffice to say I love nature and enjoy camping and hiking.  My favorite nature spot is being in the Redwoods and I never tire of Yosemite.   But there are so many other great nature places in California to visit and enjoy.

I am a non-smoker and I apologize for having a very weak immune system but I am allergic to animal dander, cigarette smoke, dust, pollen and strong scents just to name a few.  All my bedding have hypo-allergenic encasings.   As a result I cannot accept guests with pets, even if theyâ€™re a service animal or emotional support pets.  

I would appreciate confirmed guests informing me in advance of their arrival and departure schedules so I can schedule the cleaners accordingly .   

My condo is on the second floor so my address is not going to be easily visible from the street level so please the directions to my place.  The entrance to my condo complex has a white wrought iron gate with Ripley Condominiums in the front.  You will need a key to enter the gate and my condo unit so communication and coordination is critical .   

Please do not bother neighbors when you arrive or during your stay.  

Thank You and looking forward to making your acquaintance.

Cecilia aka Gina

neighborhood_overview:
GLEN PARK is really like a little village in the very center of the city. There are a variety of really good restaurants, from our authentic French bistro, Le P'tit Laurent, American fare at Chenery Park, Gialina Pizzeria, La Corneta Taqueria, Eco Sushi, and Osha Thai restaurant.

For breakfast, try Destination Bakery for fresh brioche, Tyger's Coffee Shop, or my favorite, Higher Grounds, where they serve amazing crepes.

The village has a great independent bookstore, the Bird & Beckett, and thereâ€™s live jazz on Friday and Sunday nights.

Thereâ€™s a terrific gourmet supermarket, Canyon Market (see photos). Finally, the Village has its very own Farmer's Market on Sundays, selling local produce from farms all over the Bay Area. Yummmm!

GLEN CANYON PARK: Just one block from the flat is Glen Canyon Park. Unlike any other park in the City, it is situated in a rustic canyon, with 70 bucolic acres . There are easy walking trails along Islais C
host_about:
The story of who I am, and how I came to live in this most beautiful city, can be found in my recent book of poetry, "When You Run Out of America You've Arrived in San Francisco."  It's available on Amazon.

For the past 8 seasons, I've been an Airbnb host here a Maison Swiss, and its been a wonderful experience meeting folks from all over the world.  

San Francisco has been many  charms and allures and it is my pleasure to help my guests discover them.

Stephen  Labovsky

description:
Classic San Francisco home (Edwardian) in the heart of San Francisco. Located 10 minutes walk from: Fisherman's Wharf, Little Italy, Chinatown, Coit Tower, Lombard (Crookedest) Street, great cafes and restaurants, plus the cable car stops just around the corner. SAFETY: I'm fully vaccinated against Covid. I hope that you are too. My home is a safe space for folks from all minority and marginalized groups. I welcome Guests of all races, faiths, genders and sexual orientations.

The space
ABOUT THE HOUSE

Ground floor of two story Edwardian house in a little one-block long alley in North Beach built in the early 1900's.

We share a common front door. I live upstairs and guests have exclusive use of the ground floor living area that includes your own bathroom, living room etc (please see below regarding privacy). The house is an easy 10 minutes walk to many famous San Francisco landmarks - Coit Tower, Little Italy, Washington Square Park,
neighborhood_overview: North Beach has been described as "the heart of San Francisco" and my place can be described as being in the heart of North Beach.  From the front door, it's an easy 10-15 minute walk to Little Italy, Fisherman's Wharf, Chinatown, Telegraph Hill, Lombard Street, Russian Hill etc.  Or, you can catch a bus or cable car from stops just around the corner to get to Downtown.  There are numerous great restaurants and coffee shops just a short walk away.
host_about:
I'm a retired educator living with a sweet and frisky Westie.  My past research and scholarship includes issues relating to the intersection of law with race, gender and sexuality.  I grew up in Australia but have been living in the U.S. over twenty years.  I love to cook and travel.  Local Farmers Markets are among my favorite places to visit.

Having lived in North Beach in San Francisco for over a decade, I know the City and neighborhoods (especially Little Italy and Chinatown) quite well.  So, if you have any special travel desires or if you need any advice about visiting San Francisco, I'd be more than happy to help you plan a special experience or event.  Just drop me a line before you arrive.  Ask me about my favorite Happy Hour spots!

host_about:
I'm a Bay Area Serial Internet Entrepreneur, best known for Match Online Dating, TrustArc, and now BabyQuip, baby equipment rental marketplace.   I enjoy meeting new entrepreneurs and  business people as well as tourists and work hard to be sure everyone has a positive experience in my home.  

My homes are in cities named by the Spanish for Saint Francis of Assisi:  San Francisco and Santa Fe  (Santa Fe's full name is  La Villa Real de la Santa FÃ© de San Francisco de AsÃ­s (â€œThe Royal Town of the Holy Faith of St. Francis of Assisiâ€).

My San Francisco home is on Potrero Hill.  I love the home's gardens and fantastic views which you can see from five different patios or decks.  My guests enjoy the combination of luxury and elegance with comfortable charm.

My other homes are in Santa Fe, New Mexico, where I grew up.  The two homes on Garcia St., Gorgeous on Garcia and Casa Kateri, in the Historic East Side of Santa Fe, are truly "Santa Fe Style" with vigas (ceiling beams), Kiva fireplace, wood floors and thick adobe walls.  The setting is spectacular in the heart of old Santa Fe with easy access to the museums, art, hiking trails, and plaza.  Casa Laguna is in the Quail Run resort community in Santa Fe, just a few miles from town.  There you can access the golf course, tennis/pickle ball courts, swimming pool, and wonderful trail system.

As you can see from my reviews, many first-time Airbnb guests have enjoyed my homes. If you are new to Airbnb (or not) and want to book one of my listings, please consider these 'pro tips' gleaned from my Airbnb experiences...both, as a host and as a guest:

1) Read the Airbnb FAQs thoroughly and feel free to ask questions. Hosts with popular listings appreciate it when prospective guests ask questions unique to their travel situation and/or the listing in question. 

2) PLEASE thoroughly read through my listings. I assure you that your questions about parking, public transportation, check in/out, etc. have been included in the listings.

3)  Tell me about yourself.  Since you may have few/no reviews, hosts like me must make a guess as to what sort of guest(s) you might be (and some hosts won't even consider people new to Airbnb). In the absence of a review, you might consider the following to ensure I (other hosts) will feel comfortable approving your request:

â€¢ in your initial note, it is appreciated when you include what your plans are during your stay (sightseeing, attending a conference, partying at clubs, etc) 
â€¢ include assuring comments about how you will treat my home (i.e. "I will treat your home with the same respect I treat mine") 
â€¢ let me know you've read the house rules, and that they are agreeable to you (this is a must, please)

4) Finally...I, like other busy hosts, keep my calendar up to date! So, if Airbnb is showing my listings as available for your dates - the place is available! If my listing suits your needs, it is best to send the booking request right off. If you hesitate, the other person looking at my place for your dates will get it!

Hope this is helpful. Welcome!

description:

City and County of San Francisco

The space
Stay in our comfortable home just 2.5 blocks to the Glen park BART station (the San Francisco subway system), in the quaint Glen Park neighborhood. It's a village type neighborhood with restaurants, cafes, an upscale grocery store (Canyon Market) and a beautiful 68 acre natural park with trails called Glen Canyon Park. Note: We are NOT downtown but in a quiet neighborhood of San Francisco. Please don't rate the location less than 5 stars because you had other expectations or really wanted to be in another neighborhood as some guests have done.
Downtown is only a 15 min BART ride and The Mission is a 5 min ride.
Our home is a 1908 Victorian cottage with vintage charm yet modern kitchen and bath. The room is small with stylish furnishings, including a desk. down comforter and pillows and a foa
neighborhood_overview:
I love the small town feel and charm of our little "downtown" area. I love my neighbors. I love the ease of transportation both public (BART- the train system, buses & streetcars and freeway access going both north and south. I love the 70- acre natural park called Glen Canyon Park, I love the Friday, Saturday and Sunday music at our local independent bookstore called Bird & Beckett I love our modern library and I love our high quality grocery store (Canyon Market) and the restaurants and cafÃ©s.
The Glen Park neighborhood is an urban oasis in San Francisco. We can get to the activity easily yet retreat to a quieter, slower paced environment when coming home.
host_about:
Don and I have lived in Glen Park for 30 years and in SF for more than 40. We know San Francisco very well and can help guide you with suggestions for getting around town and having fun. We're both realtors so we know neighborhoods that many long time residents have never heard of. Our schedules are flexible so we're in and out of the house and have a home office to work from but it's away from the room that's available to rent. We're low keyed, relaxed, like to BBQ and will gladly share with you if you're around. We like to meet new people, travel when we can and go to our house in Sonoma when that's not (Website hidden by Airbnb) love the City but also love the quiet of our neighborhood yet know that we're only a few BART stops away from downtown or the Mission. We can walk to our great neighborhood restaurants and cafes or hike in our hidden treasure "Glen Canyon Park". We have 2 dogs but keep them out of the room that you'd be staying in.
Please tell us about about yourself when you're inquiring about availibility or wanting to book a time. Also you must have a visiblefocused photo and your profile/description completed.

name: Lovely Private Suite Near UCSF- Monthly Only
description:
*Minimum 30-day stay

*Sound advisory:
Art, your host, is a professional percussionist and practices every evening from 5:30 - 7:00 pm in the adjacent garage. The muffled sound of Latin jazz drums and music can be heard in the suite. Otherwise it's very quiet throughout the day and night. If daily drumming bothers you, then our suite is not a good choice. Many of our guests have told us they enjoy it, but we know that tastes differ. Our pricing reflects this sound consideration.

The space
Welcome to our private and fully-equipped suite with a separate kitchen and lush garden. We're located in a safe area near restaurants, museums, transit, Golden Gate Park and U.C. San Francisco Medical Center.

BOOKING: Please have a complete profile with photo and Verified I.D. before inquiring. Since we only book long-term guests who will stay a month or more, we would like to know something about you so please write more than a few lines on your b
neighborhood_overview:
Our fully-contained suite is located in the thriving Inner Sunset district, a safe residential neighborhood and one of San Francisco's most vibrant communities. There are many options for dining and just about every type of world cuisine is found in the excellent neighborhood restaurants--this is not an exaggeration.

In addition to dining options, the area is brimming with cafes, sports bars, retail shops, a post office, hardware store, drug store, laundromats, bakeries, a grocery market, and banks all within a five minute walk from the suite. There's a bustling Farmer's Market with organic produce and fresh artisan goods every Sunday.

We have a binder in the suite with menus from the local restaurants, as well as maps and our own guidebook.

The suite is an 8-minute walk to the University of California (UCSF) campus and medical center, convenient for anyone associated with the university or in need of a place to stay close to the hospital.
host_about:
We're proud of our excellent ratings, so please take a moment to read our reviews! We strive to make your stay with us a five-star experience.

We have lived in our home for over 25 years and every day we feel fortunate that we live in beautiful San Francisco.  Our children were raised in our great neighborhood, the Inner Sunset district, and many of our neighbors are longtime friends. We're excited to share the wonders of the city to all who visit our SF Suite.

Both of us are career media professionals who have joyfully  transitioned to working in community arts organizations.  

We have visited many places in the U.S. and abroad  and our many travel experiences have given us great insight in how to host. We have always enjoyed staying in private spaces to get a feel for how the locals live. On our travels we have enjoyed cooking our own meals as well as eating out. Hopefully our guests will benefit from what we've learned along the way about hospitality and comfort. 

Our hosting style is service-oriented but not intrusive, where your privacy and comfort is our priority. We live on the premises, above the suite and are always available to help our guests have the best stay possible.  We look forward to meeting you!

~Syl and Art

name: Sweet Victorian Charmer with Views
description:
Perched high up on 28th St. with stunning views of downtown and the Bay Bridge from our dining room, living room, kitchen and deck our home can be yours while we're away in December. Parking is free and readily available - no kidding - and public transportation is so close you can see the bus stop from the front door. If you'd like to settle into our little gem after a hard day of sightseeing, let us know!

The space
Our home is more than 100 years old and we love its old world charm. It has lots of wood and lots of windows and an open floor plan so you can enjoy the panoramic view from the kitchen, dining and livingrooms. There is a wrap around deck with plants, a barbeque and a table and chairs - great for breakfast or lunch in good weather. The bedroom has a double bed and we have a double futon mattress that you're welcome to use in the living room. There is one full bathroom.

With garden, deck, and stunning views you might just want to experienc
neighborhood_overview:
We live in a great part of San Francisco. The views are lovely, the air is fresh, the people are friendly, and parking is free and readily available in our part of Noe Valley (as opposed to many other parts of our neighborhood and the city).

We're close to great dining and neighborhood shopping. 24th Street in "downtown" Noe Valley is one of the most delightful neighborhoods in San Francisco. It's like being in a small town in the midst of a big city.

We're also convenient to the "Big City" and to all parts of the Bay Area. We are close to public transportation and to highways that can easily get you to nearby cities and attractions if you have a car. (See "Getting Around" for more details.)
host_about: I'm a Yoga teacher and body movement therapist, happy to share my skills with you for a deeply discounted fee (just give me your tired, your poor). When I'm not doing yoga or helping others feel better I'm often imagining myself in a Latin American country such as Guatemala where I lived with a family and studied Spanish.  If you're up for it, I welcome the opportunity to practice with you.

description:

Please click below to learn much more about our home (including some rules and requests.)

The space
Your deluxe master suite has warm, wood-paneled walls, a king size McCroskey bed, a cozy sitting area (which folds out to become a queen size sofa bed) and a flat-screen television, with HBO. Your "en-suite" marble bathroom is highlighted by a glass tiled shower.

Double sliding doors open to your own, private garden, with old brick pathways, comfortable seating, huge lemon trees, colorful flowers, and a bright, southern exposure in one of San Francisco's sunniest neighborhoods. Be sure to sit and watch the hummingbirds feed.

I love classical music, jazz, arabic music, and traditional indian dance. My favorite travel destination: a hammock in the shade near the sea, preferably on a hill, a cold tea with lemon and sugar and a good book and also the desire to sleep without a work deadline. 
As a guest I am independent and curious. As a host I like clear communication and would like for my guest to feel at home and welcome. 
My motto: a day at the time.

Check the book "Stairway Walks in San Francisco". There are many artful stairway walks throughout the city that originate near our house. Cafe's and restaurants are a 20-30 minute walk away in any direction.

Life is Grand!

description:
Lovingly renovated Jr 1 bedroom apartment atop Billy Goat Hill offers a quiet and cozy place to call home with amazing hiking and stunning views just steps from your front door. Your small pet is welcome and this is a wonderful area to walk or play. The apartment also boasts luxury amenities such as under-floor heating, marble tiled bathroom, and a brand new kitchen. A truly unique and stylish place to stay!

The space
Completely private with street level entrance, this apartment is the lower floor of a hip, 1920's, two-story farmhouse designed by my grandmother and built using recycled cobblestones from the old railway tracks that once ran down Market Street. It was the first house built on this hill and now has been lovingly renovated throughout with luxury amenities and details.

Surrounded by nature and just steps from the wild park Billy Goat Hill with its sweeping views of the city and scenic walks of Diamond Heights and Glen Park, this unique pro
neighborhood_overview: Billy Goat Hill (named after what used to be my great-grandmother's farm) is just steps from your front door and is a walker/hiker/dog paradise. It boasts gorgeous panoramic views of San Francisco and is a lovely place to sit with a book or a friend. Just up the hill is a shopping center with a Safeway (grocery), Walgreens (drug store), post office, Chinese and Japanese restaurants, and a cafe. There are also two wonderful playgrounds within 1/4 mile for your human or four-footed children. The neighborhood is safe, quiet, and peaceful, a retreat from the hustle and bustle of the city.
host_about:
I am a 5th generation San Franciscan!  My parents and 3 brothers all still live in the heart of San Francisco.  I am a violinist (fiddle player actually, I specialize in Irish music) and I travel a lot...  My husband is Swiss, and a winemaker and our family spends a fair amount of time in Italy.  Our 2 daughters travel with us, attending schools in Italy, the US and a month or so in Haiti where we have a foundation called Te Soley.   Our beautiful San Francisco home is our little retreat, a tranquil refuge from busy airports and often exhausting adventures around the world.  We are delighted to be able to share our little gem with other couples and families who are also looking for a tranquil, beautiful place to call home while they explore the riches of San Francisco and Northern CA.
Athena

neighborhood_overview: The Mission is bursting with life. There are so many different cultures mixing it up here. People are friendly, the restaurants are fantastic, the murals are incredible and the vibe is exciting. There are around 75 restaurants within walking distance of our home. Plus there are always new shops and restaurants opening up on Mission and Valencia Streets. Urban Putt, an indoor mini golf course with a restaurant (that's good) is just 3 blocks away. A pirate store (Paxton Gate) on Valenica. And the Alamo Cinema Draft House, a stunningly restored historic 1930's theater featuring first run movies, cult classics, and offers reserved seating with bar (fantastic cocktails and craft beer list, wine too) and full menu service (not typical movie theater fare) right to your seat in the theater. Be sure to check out the Bear vs. Bull, a cool bar inside the Alamo Theater building. Advanced screenings, celebrity appearances, and other special events too. Download their free app and order tickets in a
host_about:
My wife and I have traveled the world, but have called San Francisco home for 25 years. We invite you to stay with us in our 1896 Edwardian home in the middle of the Mission District, San Francisco's oldest and arguably most vibrant neighborhood filled with a diverse range of some of the City's best restaurants, bars, parks, shops, and more. Not to mention our neighborhood is the warmest, flattest, and fog free part of San Francisco. 

We're 15 minutes from SFO by taxi, a block and a half from the 24th Bart Station and close to many bus and MUNI (subway) lines. Having visited Southeast Asia, Oceania, Australia, Europe, Central America, and of course all over North America, one theme holds true for all our adventures: discover the true culture and flavor wherever we are. 

As your host, we'll do everything we can to make sure you get off the beaten path. We're happy to share our favorite restaurants, local hangouts, and ensure you see the true San Francisco, not just the typical touristy sites. We're into everything from scuba diving, biking, kayaking, hiking, wine, art, music, food, festivals, museums, all things teens, parks, and more. Whatever you're into, we'll point you in the right direction so you have an authentic and memorable time in San Francisco. My motto is from the great Mahatma Ghandi: "Be the change you wish to see in the world." Our style of hosting reflects the needs of our guests. When possible, we like to meet our guests. However we understand that many of them are busy on a tight schedule or not interested to meet us so we respect that. We want to make sure every guest is comfortable and part of that is respecting boundaries and their personal space. 

We look forward to hosting you soon! If you have any questions, please feel free to ask. We're just a click away.

-Mickey

description:

The space
The Royal Exchange Insurance Building is an historic San Francisco Landmark. This unique building was the first commercial building completed downtown after the 1906 earthquake. In 2006, it was converted to condominiums. The brick and stone facade remain unchanged. The marble and glass entry is also an exquisite time piece. Much of the marble was imported from Milan, Italy. Marble staircases are still in use between floors. There is a gorgeous common roof terrace with mature flowering and edible plants, seating and lounging areas. This tenth floor unit is in the rear of the building, and has excellent sunlight. The original warehouse style bay windows are an historic part of this unit.

A dream setting. San Francisco living at it's BEST.

neighborhood_overview:
Pacific Heights is one of the nicest historic neighborhoods that is centrally located in San Francisco.
Walking distance to five grocery stores - three blocks to either Whole Foods (one the corner or California street and Franklin street) or Molly Stones (on California street, after you pass Fillmore street). To mor4 blocks to Trader Joeâ€™s and two Safewayâ€™s - I e south and one north from my home, 5 minutes drive. Also fun grocery Japanese supermarket - 3 blocks and another ethnic one - Woori, Korean market.

Itâ€™s a great place to hike and run. I usually run to the Bay and sometimes to the Golden Gate Bridge and back through Lyon Stairs. Very scenic route. There are lost of beautiful parks close to my home. The closest park is just a 1.5 blocks away - on Laguna and Sacramento street.

My home is located close to the famous Fillmore Street and an easy walk to Union Street. Both streets are a shopping heaven. Also there are many great restaurants walking distan
host_about:
I am a physician and I moved to USA 22 years ago. I love what San Francisco city and the Bay Area has to offer. I feel very lucky and privileged to live in a beautiful and safe area of San Francisco called Pacific Heights. 

I am an avid mountaineer/climber and I travel usually once a year, for a month - long expedition trip. That is usually when I open the calendar in AirBnB for my apartment, as well as (separately) for my garage. 

I would like to rent my beautiful home to someone reliable for all that time when I am gone. 

The things I can't live without are my family, friends, mountains, my amazing home, nature, meditation and any kind of physical activity daily. 

My favorite travel destinations - to many to mention. I feel amazing in high altitude mountains. 

I climbed all the highest mountains in the world called Seven Summits (including Mt.Everest), as well as skied to the South Pole.  Beside that, all my travels and expeditions left me with amazing memories. 

My favorite books - too many to list here as I  read a lot, but I love the most  "Master and Margarita" by Michail Bulhakov. There are many books in my home, so if you have time feel free to read something new. I switched now to ebooks or audiobooks, as it doesn't take any physical space. 

My favorite food is prepared with local and organic ingredients - check out many restaurants on Fillmore street - you will have so many to choose from, even after Pandemic years. I love sushi and the best sushi in the city is a walking distance from my home - check out Tataki restaurant (on California street/Divisadero street) - amazing and fresh! 
I also would encourage you to check â€œState Bird Provisionsâ€, but you would need a reservation. Itâ€™s a 7 -10 minutes walking distance from my home. Located on Fillmore street. 

I travel a lot for business - Marriott hotels, but for fun - I prefer staying in a tent or in a cool Airbnb place in different cities all over the world. 

My motto in life is to live largely, â€œon the edge of my comfort zone", hence climbing or polar expeditions, and now posting my home at Airbnb website. 

Throughout the process of renting my home I learn that my HOAâ€™s CC&Rs (Homeowners Rules) do not allow for any short term rentals and I can only rent it for a month or longer. 

My modern apartment is located on the top floor of the beautiful Victorian (freshly painted) building (originally from 1896). I have the best view of Japan Town and Twin Towers as well as complete privacy in my home. 

I love green plants and I have many in my home and at the balcony. Iâ€™ll be very grateful if you could please water it once a week ( just a little bit :) to keep it lush and green. 

So far, I had wonderful guests from all over the world for the last ten years. I am super grateful for all people I met through AirBnB. 

Please feel free to ask me any questions before you send a reservation. 

I look forward to meeting you in person and to host you in my home.
 
Thank you.

host_about:
I moved from my native country of Japan to the Russian Hill neighborhood of San Francisco over 20 years ago and I plan to stay here forever. I truly love San Francisco and Russian Hill in particular. I manage my own art business and love collecting and restoring antiques. I also love traveling, wine tasting, hiking, visiting museums and galleries, cooking, and checking out new San Francisco restaurants and coffee shops.

I am passionate about respecting and maintaining San Franciscoâ€™s old world charm. I personally restored this property, keeping as much of the original details that I could while creating a comfortable atmosphere with modern conveniences. I want guests to have an authentic San Francisco experience, and hope the space I have created will make you feel at home. 

Because I have lived here for so long, I can provide guests with tips on sites and local restaurants that are off of the beaten path. I can also recommend neighborhood walks that expose guests to the historic and cultural charm that San Francisco has to offer. Since I often go to Napa and Sonoma, I have many recommendations of wineries that you may want to visit. 

I am proud of my adopted city and my home and want to share them with you. I hope that you can experience all the wonders of San Francisco that I am so lucky to enjoy everyday.

If you like my property, please add it to your Wish List!

name: Wild Garden unit  (coders' paradise, 1000 sq .ft.)
description:
Powered by the nearest star, taken over by wild backyard vegetation, the place is a dream destination for the writer, coder, or just anyone who yearns quietude in a spaciously modern living environment we refer to as "A Little Bit of San Francisco." A combo front door lock, a keyed inner door, and latched glass rear patio doors open into this very large and modernized unit to settle into. Will even help set your cell phone to remotely lock/unlock the outer, ground-level front door and more.

The space
Our apartment (1100 sq. ft) is fully furnished with tatami bed, 2 sofa beds and lounge chair .Additional fold-out bed available upon request . Galley kitchen has granite countertops, stainless steel appliances and fully stocked with all kitchen utensils. HD TV/Netflix subscription, in-suit washer/dryer , iron/ironing board. We also provide all linen and towels.

Other supplies include: paper towels & tissue, soap for dishes/dish washer/clothes wash
neighborhood_overview:
Neighborhood is a mix of incoming professionals, often computer programmers and network technologists, according to recent news reports. The charm, we think, lies in the spirits and values of those residents who have been here for decades, some as far back as the 1950s.

Their presence seems to stimulate a "small-townish" blend of values and family spirit. There's a feeling of balance that weighs down the hustle and bustle of those others whose minds are filled with programming and itineraries.

And that's the magic of San Francisco, the blend or mergence of itineraries into a sort of City mindset.

name: Spacious Gem to Entertain or Relax
description:
Our home is a perfect spot for a family or group of friends visiting SF: equipped with an open-layout, modern kitchen/dining room; walking distance to a supermarket, drugstore, and Starbucks; and ample parking or easy access to public transportation.

The space
Our home is an immaculate Spanish style home with 1800 sq ft of finished space in charming Old Miraloma. Our 2-level corner property features lots of natural light, vaulted ceilings, parquet floors, recessed lighting, and views of Mt. Davidson. The eat-in Chef's kitchen includes stainless steel appliances, custom cabinets, slate tile floor, and a granite island and breakfast bar with large skylight. The dining area and living room with fireplace and flatscreen are also on the main level, along with a remodeled tile-and-marble bathroom with Jacuzzi and glass shower stall. Two bedrooms are on this same level, with one set up as a proper guestroom with Queen, and the other as a nursery (with crib). This bedro
neighborhood_overview: Miraloma Park is a residential neighborhood that has old San Francisco charm. (Our home was built in 1937, for example.) In our central location, you are close to the action but not in the action. Our home is a short bus ride or cab ride away from fun neighborhoods like the Castro and the Mission so you can go out to dinner and drinks but then return to a quiet refuge after a day of activities. It's close to public transportation which makes reaching downtown simple and quick. There is a shopping center with a grocery store, a sandwich shop, a burger joint, a pizza place, a drug store, and a Starbucks right behind our house. And if you want to experience nature there are many trails at Mt. Davidson and in Glen Canyon Park, both right in our 'hood, that are perfect for that morning jog or urban hike!
host_about:
I am a proud resident of the vibrant City by the Bay!  After growing up on the East Coast, I moved to SF in my early 20's, and here I am, 7 years later and still loving every moment here.  My husband Chris and I are now in our 30's, and as much as we enjoy our time in San Francisco, we spend many weekends visiting friends & family, skiing in Tahoe and traveling to new places.  We bought a beautiful home last year and want to join AirBnB so others can take advantage of our great place while we're away.

More about us...during the week, Chris is a high school teacher and I work at a hedge fund.  Our weekends in town often involve dance music, watching sporting events, and  doing activities like tennis and cycling to stay healthy together.  We love the big, fun network of energetic SF friends that always keeps us on our toes.  We are excited about the opportunity to meet new folks through airbnb and to help visitors have the best time ever while in SF.

name: Cottage in the Mission
description:
A large pleasant private bedroom in the carriage house at the rear of a SF Victorian on a quiet tree lined street. Hardwood floors, windows look out on sunny courtyard, which is yours to enjoy as well!
Listing ID: STR-010853

The space
Come stay in our secluded cottage in the heart of the Mission district, the sunniest neighborhood in San Francisco. There are many micro-climates of SF and the mission's geographical location insulates it from the fog and cold air of the west, keeping in warm and sunny most of the year.

Spend your time tucked away in our courtyard/ garden oasis, where you'll relax in the sun along side jasmine, french lavender, trumpet flowers, and wisteria with friendly kitties to keep you company.

Built in 1905, this cozy cottage situated on a quiet tree lined block, has everything you'll need for an unforgettable stay in San Francisco! All with in one block you can find nice new local restaurants, coffee houses, a bar

The space
This studio with private entrance is super cute â€” the perfect place to land when you are done seeing every corner of the City. We are close to lots of fun stuff AND good public transportation.

Pristine studio apartment with fully-equipped kitchen, huge closet and backyard deck. neighborhood_overview:
Nestled at the base of Bernal Hill and half a block from Precita Park, this part of Bernal Heights is close to Muni, BART, and the Mission. Precita Park Cafe is 100 steps from the apartment, while nearby Harvest Hills Market offers organic delights.

The apartment is walking distance from many restaurants, bars and shopping. We are one block from the Mission, known for its great dining (including the best burritos in the world), cool bars and unique shopping. It's a perfectly flat walk into the Mission from the apartment so no need to worry about hills in that direction.

Walk South and you will end up on Bernal Hill with 360 degree views of the city (from the very top) and a cool hill top swing that has you soaring over rooftops and flying over a magnificent view of downtown. A little further and you arrive at Cortland Ave, our little village with quaint restaurants and shops.
host_about:
Hi, I'm Jennifer. I'm a graphic designer and illustrator and I work at home. I live with my partner, Christian and I have two grown kids - both who live on their own.

I love to read, paint and walk. I'm a huge Outlander and Jane Austen fan. Besides San Francisco, Paris is my favorite city. I haven't traveled as much as I'd like - I'm hoping to do a lot more in the future. My guests inspire me to see the world! 

2023 marks my 11th year as a host! I had no idea what to expect when I started, but I really love it and when you visit you will see that I put my heart and soul into the apartment and making sure you have a great stay.

I have lived in Bernal Heights since 1991 and I adore it. It's a really cute neighborhood with lots of great, thoughtful people. 

The apartment is an in-law in my house. It used to be my office until I realized that I really only need a computer to work and the space was going to waste. A friend came in and redesigned the space for me specifically as a vacation rental (I helped!) and he did a beautiful job. 

Hosting happy guests is my number one priority and all the good reviews really make my day. Come and stay!

Buena Vista Park is just a couple of blocks up the hill surrounded by amazing archictectural gems and breathtaking views of the city and the bay.  Duboce Park a block away is also surrounded by such quaint beautiful houses that they are on the tour bus route (those buses avoid our block because of our short  hill, keeping this section of our street a quiet secret!)  Yet with Haight St and Divisadero just a block away, public transportation, grocery stores, cafes and restaurants abound within a short walk.
host_about:
I came to San Francisco for the first time many years ago to visit my daughter.  I couldn't visit for long, sleeping in her and her roommate's living room. Time together was precious, hotels were too far and too expensive.  My dream of owning a house close to daughter and grandchildren came true.
  I am now  living the dream of hosting fellow visiting parents and grandparents, in addition to vacationers, business travelers,  individuals and families the world over.  I really enjoy sharing my house and my city.
My husband and I love family, friends, music, nature, great food and wine, old movies, sports.  We are hikers, birders and world travelers.  We appreciate cultural diversity and individual uniqueness.
My motto:  Dream it, love it, expect it, and you will experience it!

Welcome to the Pierce Street Suite, which occupies the entire top-floor attic of a 1897 Queen Anne Victorian, right in the heart of San Francisco's Lower Haight. The house was built just a few years after street car service came to Haight Street. The neighborhood was considered "the country"; the street car service opened it up to "city" residents.

The space
First, the space you'll be occupying: bright and airy, clean and cozy. The attic (formerly used for storage, guests, and a playroom complete with trapeze) was remodeled in October 2012. The original plan was that it would be occupied by the daughter of the house who had decided to return to San Francisco from Italy where she had lived for 12 years. host_about:
I'm an enthusiastic bicyclist who worked  as a family lawyer to keep myself in bike socks.  Born in San Francisco, grew up near Stanford University, and moved around a lot before I got back to San Francisco in 1976. I've raised two children in this house and they've always claimed they grew up in the best neighborhood in San Francisco. 

Since both my children live elsewhere (but have left their hearts in San Francisco), I'm now occupying this 4-story Victorian on my own, though there are often friends and relatives visiting who stay in the main part of the house.  . I love meeting new people, but can assure you that you'll have plenty of privacy, as the Attic Suite is on the top floor and is quite separate from the main house. 

I travel often to Italy to visit my daughter  and granddaughter who is now 7. A long, long time ago, I spent two years living and teaching in Africa.  

This is a wonderful city and a dynamic, friendly neighborhood that I feel fortunate to live in and share.

description:
The space
If you are looking for a cozy, comfortable, clean and friendly place to hang out while you are in SF we have the one for you. We are just one block from Alamo Square Park and the Painted Ladies with bus lines crossing at the corner and others within easy walking distance. Parking can be tricky, we now have 2 hour parking limits from 9 to 6. Because public transportation is so accessible and there are taxis, Lyft and Uber it is easy to get where you need to go around town.
Up the street and around the corner you find the joys of Divisidero St., with coffee shops, restaurants, clubs and a variety of stores. Golden Gate Park is about 5 blocks away, a good walk, or by Bus, an easy ride.
The room has a comfortable queen bed, good lighting and plenty of books for R&R and fast WiFi connection.
There is a bath and two w c's down the hall, a nice kitchen, living room and a laundry for you to use. There are three friendly people living here and we h
neighborhood_overview:

host_about:
I have been a happy resident of San Francisco since 1994, living right here on McAllister St where I arrived after a former life-time married to a fine man, raising a family of three sons.
I came for a visit and decided to stay......San Francisco does that to you.  I spent my early years here touring the city on inline skates, yes, hills and flat....great adventures, great friends, did the Friday Night Skate for years.   My work and rental property take my time and the fact that I now have 5 dear grandchildren living around the country means I travel rather often.  Now I walk everywhere with Muni as a backup.  SF is a great place to walk, you are never at a loss to find interesting places, beautiful buildings and lovely parks, beaches, trails, whatever your heart desires.  Good way to keep healthy, too, with yoga and gardening added for balance.  I have been renting rooms in my place since 1997 when I was able to purchase it.  I have had hundreds of people stay since then, many from other countries.  I have furnished rooms and cater to students, interns, people new to the city, beginning jobs.....a good place to get a start and figure out where you want to stay more permanently.  I try to make it a home away from home for them.  For me it is like having a large, ever changing family.
Because of the changing politics throughout the world, much of which is troubling,  as angry people take over governments and spread upset and anger about, I think it is valuable to have platforms such as Airbnb bringing people together from everywhere.  The chance to meet, talk, share a meal, converse with a group of people from different countries has to be good for our world.  I have a large map of the world in the living room and each guest puts a pin in the country from which they come.  It is thrilling to see the map fill and know that we have had good times with friends from all of those places!

host_about:
My Motto; "Every Day is a Good Day!"

*As of February 27, 2022  I was fully vaccinated by way of the Pfizer all available vaccine and the two boosters available. I also contracted Covid 19 or a variant in May 2022 and fully recovered.

Something about me and my home; Iâ€™m gay, 64, single, very fit and energetic, very outgoing and easy going. I have always lived in California and have traveled the world extensively. I absolutely love San Francisco and even more being in the Mission District. Entrepreneurial spirited, at age twenty-one I started a business which fulfilled insurersâ€™ responsibilities for auto losses involving vandalism and retired from that adventure just shy of 36 years later.  I have been vegan for four years now and I have redirected my culinary skills towards all things plant, sugar-free, and fat-free based cuisine.  I enjoy practicing yoga at Love Story just around the corner.  I am also an avid bicyclist and use my bike as my primary mode of transport in the city.  I am attending  Community College SF working my way to a zoological degree. Life is good.

As for my home, the location and views are arguably the best the Mission District can offer. The private roof deck, a green oasis for the otherwise concrete jungle of a Mission Street residence. My place faces west so it's on the street side and is usually quite noisy from people, traffic and sirens. Thankfully the residence was constructed in 2008 and  built  quite soundproof. The bedrooms are well sized and comfortably appointed. The sun always seems to shine in the Mission District.

Finally, I love being an AirBnB host which allows me to share my good fortune, meet wonderful people and make new friends. 

I hope that you choose to stay. 

Mark

neighborhood_overview:
About the Inner Mission District-
"La Mision" / The MIssion
Centrally located close to downtown, it is the city's Latino district & has been the gateway for most new immigrants, initially Italian, Irish, then predominantly Latino since the 1970's .
It is famous for its historic buildings, Mission burritos (the best in Northern California), grungy artistic scene & it's colorful murals.
Though the Mission still retains it's gritty 'barrio' (hood) flavor the neighborhood has been undergoing a second wave of gentrification, experiencing with an influx of techn money.
The Mission district is large & complex, with varying socioeconomic areas, clusters of mini-communities, and specialty stores found nowhere else. A few years back Utne Reader rated the Inner Mission the 2nd coolest place to live in the US (first was New Orlean's Garden District).
Like in any other cities there are sections of the Mission that can be high crime but don't let that scare you, a
host_about:
Hola! 
I love to travel, the last place I went was the Caribbean in Honduras (awesome) &  I have been day dreaming about my next destination-Colombia.  I also love to dance-all kinds but Samba is my religion!

For an authentically Mission experience there is a free Salsa lesson included in your stay- I can teach you in 15 mins -yes  it's that easy & just enough to fake the rest...
I also love gardening, culture, fashion, camping, history and living in SF.
I like Airbnb because I can taste the travel energy without the actual travel, I have met very interesting & wonderful people & I love showing guests the best of SF life.   The best compliment I can receive is when my guests want to return, it makes me happy.  

For 23 years, I owned one of the last Latin cultural stores in the community, it was a landmark legacy business which gave me a very intimate & spiritual connection to the Mission- hence why I  was  picked to film an Airbnb success story commercial you may have seen on u-tube called 
"Airbnb Nancy" - what a blast! 
 
You can also see the guide I made for Airbnb's  Mission Institutions:

name: Unique Home, Magical Garden, Amazing Views + Tub!
description:
Located in the heart of San Francisco atop beautiful Bernal Heights, our unique and colorful home offers a true San Francisco experience. Our Magical Garden retreat is a hidden oasis. Enjoy amazing Golden Gate Bridge and skyline vistas from any of our eight levels. Soak under the stars in our beautiful outdoor tub while marveling at the sparkling city lights. The summit of Bernal Hill is at our door for a hike or a run and offers a 360Â° vista of the city and unforgettable sunsets.

The space
DUE TO THE COVID 19 OUTBREAK WE ARE TAKING EXTRA CARE TO DISINFECT ALL SURFACES BETWEEN RESERVATIONS. WE GUARANTEE A HIGH LEVEL OF CLEANLINESS/DISINFECTION.

Our unique, eclectic home with it's Magical Garden serves as a sweet retreat in the heart of San Francisco. It would be perfect for business team building, as a yoga retreat, for a reunion, for a friends or family get together or just as a sanctuary to return to after a day of exploring our beautiful cit
neighborhood_overview:
Bernal Heights has some of the best weather in San Francisco. It also has the best views and has a safe, friendly village feel to it.

Our "main street" Cortland Avenue has a little of everything, including several world class restaurants.

Right outside our door is Bernal Hill, a beautiful piece of parkland that affords a 360Âº view of San Francisco. If you are lucky you may see one of our local coyotes. Come here for sunrise, sunset or for star gazing!

Don't miss our Alemany Market which becomes a fabulous Farmers Market on Saturdays and a Flea Market on Sundays.
host_about:
Hi, I'm Jeannie.  My husband, Skate and I love to host guests in our beautiful home.  
 
We provide our guests with privacy while also offering travel and local recommendations based upon our 40+ years as San Franciscans.  We love meeting new people and making new friends.

Skate and I have travelled extensively throughout Europe, Asia, Middle East, Africa and North, Central and South America.  We love to explore back roads, back alleys and back woods. We can be exhausting to travel with! 

One of our favorite things to do is to travel simply by either camping or staying in local homes so that we get to really experience the culture and people of the region we are visiting.
 
We enjoy spending time in our garden and with our family, we also enjoy eating good food, traveling to new and exciting destinations, camping, sunshine and live music which you may hear Skate playing!
 
For us Airbnb is a wonderful way to travel but also through hosting a way to meet new people from all over the world while staying at home!

Skate and I look forward to meeting you!

description:
The private room is in a remodeled 2 BR 1.5 BA condo in a 1903 Victorian home, located on a quiet hillside lane above the historic Haight Ashbury district. Walk just 2 blocks up the hill and you'll arrive at Buena Vista Park offering stunning vistas of the entire city. Walk just 2 blocks down, and you'll arrive at the bustling Haight Street with restaurants, bars, and grocery stores all within easy reach. Many public transportation options, and close to all major San Francisco attractions.

The space
Space details: Second floor room in rear of home, medium-sized (about 12' x 12') with closet, high ceilings, hardwood floors, floor to ceiling windows looking out onto lush backyards, space heater provided. Furnished with full-sized bed, bedside table and lamp, small writing desk with chair, and luggage rack.

Guest access
Guests have access to the first floor (bedroom, half-bath, living/dining room, kitchen), and to the shower upstairs. Pl
neighborhood_overview: Vibrant with colorful shops, restaurants and bars, San Francisco's Haight-Ashbury neighborhood boasts unique businesses from its 60â€™s heyday and today.  Brightly painted Victorian era architecture abounds in the Haight.  For historic points of interest in the neighborhood, pick up a neighborhood map at any of the small corner markets on Haight Street for the locations of the former homes of icons such as Janis Joplin, Jimi Hendrix,  and the Grateful Dead.  Golden Gate Park with its many attractions borders the western edge of the neighborhood.  The city's oldest park, Buena Vista Park is on the eastern edge offering a  steeply sloped wooded park with hiking trails and views over the entire city.  The popular Panhandle section of Golden Gate Park is just a few blocks to the north.
host_about: San Francisco attorney, originally from St. Louis, but have lived in San Francisco for 25 years.

Queen sized beds are in both the bedrooms with new, comfortable mattresses that ar
neighborhood_overview: The Ingleside Neighborhood is a true gem; it is a dynamic yet serene neighborhood in San Francisco. It has the urban beat, yet our neighborhood is completely residential. Our neighbors range from recently immigrated families, families that have lived in their home for more than 40 years, hipsters, artists, people working in the tech industry, youthful millionaires, and educators and environmental workers (like us).
host_about:
We are a couple who love the possibility of exposing young people to creative endeavors of all sorts. Debolina is a high school environmental science and biology teacher who loves to help students bring out their inner nerd. Adam is an environmental engineer. He will save the world by keeping our water clean. Yosh is an exuberant kid who is busy seeing how many minecraft worlds she can build and finding things to take apart and (hopefully) reassemble.  Jaya sees art in everything. She spends much of her time in her art studio creating works of art. The kids love to bounce on the trampoline and explore the world!

We love our neighborhood and the diversity it affords our city. Our favorite weekend morning activity is going to Philz coffee on the way to a local park. Yosh gets an opportunity to perfect his tricycling skills.

One of the perks about being teachers is that we are able to travel quite a bit. As a result, we have collectively been to over 35 countries. We also enjoyed a GAP year, and traveled around the world while in our early 30s. 

We are delighted to open our home to you so that you can enjoy this fantastic city and fabulous neighborhood. 

Welcome!

The space

neighborhood_overview:
A little about the Mission:
This is hands-down the best place to be in San Francisco. You will be in the center of it all.

The Mission is one of the culinary Hot Spots of America, and you will be surrounded by innovative restaurants, cafes, and bars that range from the affordable to the posh. Every ethnic cuisine is represented, although Pancho Villa's burrito reigns supreme. Within two blocks are Flour and Water, Penne Roma, Tartine, Atlas Cafe, Pho On Bryant, Salumeria, San Han Wo, True Laurel Bar, Trick Dog Bar, The Morris, Sightglass Coffee, Farmhouse Thai. Yelp any of these places and you'll understand why you're in Foodie nirvana. Our #1 thing to do is to have an impromptu picnic at Dolores Park in the late afternoon. There you will find a true cross-section of the Mission.

Our specific area is called the

Hi there,
I am a healer, working with Hospice. I am inspired to drink life up, understanding that there is a finite amount of life to be had. I love to travel. My last amazing journey was to the Amazon. But I bet if you talked to my friends, they'd note the overall goofy, delighted way I like to carry on with life in general. As Helen Keller said, "Life is a banquet, but most of us are starving to death." So I invite you to come to my home and take a big bite out of life. The time is now.

There is a supermarket that stays open late, post office, 24 hour Walgreens, and a wide variety of restaurants to choose from. The Castro Theatre and all the charm of the neighborhood is at your reach.

I am offering my very spacious bedroom. It's big, boasts south facing windows, a fireplace (that works but I do no
neighborhood_overview: One of the most vibrant and well known neighborhoods of San Francisco, the Castro has a lot of good restaurants and things to do nearby. Our block is just a couple of blocks away from the hustle and bustle of the Main Street. So we have the best of both worlds!
host_about:
NYer lliving in San Francisco.  Love to dance....salsa, African-based, Peruvian folkloric and kizomba, semba, collegiate shag, and modern (Dunham, Silvestre, Horton), and any conscious movement.  I am an actor and also do attorney work (mostly in Portuguese), teach dance and yoga (RYT 200), perform and co-create.  Love to travel and learn and improve communicating in different languages (English, Spanish, French, Mandarin Chinese, Portuguese, and Cape Verdean Creole....I just started learning German! and I also want to begin learning Quechua and Arabic!).  Love meditation, yoga, acro yoga, aerial yoga, being a vegan, all animals (including humans), mindfulness, nature, drawing, meditative doodling, music, chanting, singing, conscious and healing sounds, bootcamps ;-), and films that inspire or offer new perspectives, and reading....love reading!  And writing too!  I love jungles and humidity and never need airconditioning!  or even fans!  

I will be traveling often this year so this seems like a perfect fit. 

As our guest, you will have a lovely room, free washer (no dryer -- just air dry), wireless internet, shoeless household, and lovely roommates. We keep our space clean and pretty chill (no parties just occasional friends over) and peaceful!  Everyone always gets a great vibe from our place and rapport.  We hope you will too!   

Love to meet travelers as I'm an avid traveler myself and have often stayed at private houses.  I find those are the best experiences.  Doing this is my way of keep the circle turning.  I hope that your stay with me will add to your fond memories of the lovely San Francisco!

neighborhood_overview:
THE NEIGHBORHOOD

The Inner Richmond is one of the most popular, convenient neighborhoods in San Francisco:
- Three blocks from Golden Gate Park, specifically near Conservatory of Flowers, The California Academy of Sciences, De Young Museum, Japanese Gardens, and Botanical Gardens.
- Three blocks from Clement Street, including its fabulous restaurants (such as Burma Superstar, B Star, Richmond Republic, Giorgio's Pizza, Toy Boat Dessert), many coffee shops, See's Candies, bakeries, Green Apple Bookstore (regularly voted best used bookstore in SF), spas, and more.
- The Inner Richmond is home to the "other" or "real" Chinatown: less touristy than downtown, amazing food (restaurants and Asian supermarkets), fun shops.
- Six blocks from USF's huge and beautiful Koret Health and Recreation Center, for all your exercise needs.
- Five blocks from the Presidio, where you can experience breath-taking views, hikes, golf, and, of course, the Golden Gate
host_about:
We are a married couple, with two children. Our hopes, at that time, was that one day, we would own our own home, and meet and host visitors from all over. 

In 2011, we moved from NYC to San Francisco.  We bought our dream home in September, 2012.  We enjoy playing host and welcoming visitors into our home and suggesting great places to visit while staying in the San Francisco area.

We love partner dancing, especially lindy hop.

This pocket neighborhood has an outsized healthcare and education presence â€“ both the UCSF Laurel Heights Campus and California Pacific Medical Center call Laurel Heights home, and the University of San Francisco is blocks away. Health benefits extend to the Presidioâ€™s plentiful green space, well-maintained Laurel Hill Playground and Tennis Court, and the JCCSF pool.

Stores, restaurants, and shopping are found on bustling Geary Boulevard, boutique- and cafÃ©-lined Sacramento Street, and California Streetâ€™s Laurel Village Shopping Center (home to Cal-Mart, an Ace Hardware, and plenty of restaurants). neighborhood_overview:
LOCATION:
--The main entrance to Golden Gate Park is just a couple blocks away. So, very easy to walk to the California Academy of Sciences, DeYoung Museum, Japanese Tea Gardens, Botanical Gardens, Arboretum, Carousel, and a couple of different playgrounds.
--Tons of great restaurants, coffee shops, crepe places, nail salons, book stores, and cute shops and clothing boutiques within a couple of blocks. host_about:
I love to travel and fell in love with San Francisco on a trip and just had to move here!  I'm so happy and proud to be a San Franciscan!  I love sharing the city's beautiful landscape, neighborhoods and culture with first-time visitors and long-term residents alike.  

My family and I own several apartments that we have restored with love and care.  Our furnished apartments are always rented out long-term.  When we have a short gap between renters, we occasionally are able to offer a unit on Airbnb.  Sometimes, it's even a way to find great tenants--especially for those that like to "try before they buy."  

There are lots of great and useful ways to use Airbnb to help San Francisco's new, existing and future residents.  My goal is to insure guests have an excellent and authentic SF experience, and that they discover a few reasons that they might want to call SF home!
